SIMPLE: damnation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Damnation
<hw>Dam*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>damnation</ets>, L. <ets>damnatio</ets>, fr. <ets>damnare</ets>.
See <er>Damn</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being damned;
condemnation; openly expressed disapprobation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Condemnation to everlasting
punishment in the future state, or the punishment itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How can ye escape the <qex>damnation</qex> of hell?</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. xxiii. 33.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wickedness is sin, and sin is <qex>damnation</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A sin deserving of everlasting punishment.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The deep <qex>damnation</qex> of his taking-off.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Damnatory</ent>⟦br⟧
